==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''intellegentia'', '''intelligence''' (''intellegentia'' comes from ''inter''-"between" + ''legere''-"choose, pick out, [[read]]"'' inter-lege-nt-ia'', literally "choosing between").

===Noun===
'''intelligence'''

# Capacity to [[understand]] and [[comprehend]].
# Capacity to [[solve]] problems.

====Synonyms====
*[[wit]]
*[[intellect]]
*[[brightness]]

